WTC International N.V. said ithas sold its affiliates in South Africa to an independenttrust, created to continue the operations in that country.    The purchase price was about 8.4 mln dlrs, represented by aten-year interest-bearing note, payable annually at 11 pct, tobe paid by the trust out of proceeds from the South Africanoperations, the company said.    WTC said its board concluded in view of the social,political and economic situatin in South Africa, it was best toseparate the company from its interests there. Reuter&#3;